        <abstract> 
<p>The <hi rend="italic">Acacia</hi> must be Belt’s "Bulls’ horns".</p>  
<p>The complexity of <hi rend="italic">Utricularia</hi> has driven Frank and CD almost mad. Suspects it is necrophagous, i.e., it cannot digest, but absorbs decaying animal matter.</p>  
<p>Foster is certainly in error. Every insect that <hi rend="italic">Drosera</hi> catches causes aggregation.</p> 
        </abstract>
